The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 16 November is 102,593 (11,824.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 11 November, there were 4,297 new confirmed cases (495.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 04 November, there were 4,324 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 1% (27 fewer cases).
